track_notes: Plenty of parking on the grass where the public road ends. This does not start as a public right of way, but there appears to be no objection if you walk up through the first couple of fields to reach the access land.  Continue through gates to the col. Just beyond the fence on the col you can turn right (west) over a small stile. Take care to find the path up the slope to the summit. Good trig for antennas.

Cheeky parking spot 163m up the unclassified road towards Pentre-tai-yn-y-cwm. Follow Nant Cwm-da northwards. Lots of sheep. Squishy ground. Very old track, gets a bit lost towards the top. Eventually this joins with the path from the north.

I took this in descent - see Cwm Da track. Instead of the valley this takes the parallel route up the shoulder of the hills, first onto Bryn Bras then Orddu. There is yet another parish boundary stone near where you turn west at the top. I preferred this to the valley route as it is a lot firmer under foot.

Total time (including ops): 1hr 20m. Maximum difficulty: Swiss Alpine Club Grade T1. Uncurated GPX which may contain navigation errors, detours and hazards. Additional route information may be available at www.m1hax.uk. Track data by Richard M1HAX licensed under Creative Commons BY-NC-SA.
